HEADWORD: Aphis lion
<hw>A"phis li"on</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The larva
of the lacewinged flies (<spn>Chrysopa</spn>), which feeds voraciously
upon aphids. The name is also applied to the larv⟦ae⟧ of the ladybugs
(<gen>Coccinella</gen>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aphlogistic</ent>⟦br⟧
